org.eclipse.cdt.core.options

Interface OptionStorage

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    OsgiPreferenceStorage

    public interface OptionStorage
    Provides metadata-based access to an enclosed storage of options.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <V> boolean consumable(Class<V> valueType)
      Checks if the value type can be consumed by an enclosed storage.
      <V> V load(OptionMetadata<V> option)
      Loads the value of specified option from an enclosed storage.

    • Method Detail

      • consumable

        <V> boolean consumable(Class<V> valueType)
        Checks if the value type can be consumed by an enclosed storage.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the value type for the option
        Parameters:
        valueType - the value type to be checked
        Returns:
        true if this value type can be consumed by an enclosed storage and false otherwise

      • load

        <V> V load(OptionMetadata<V> option)
        Loads the value of specified option from an enclosed storage. If the value is not found returns the option default value.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the value type for the option
        Parameters:
        option - the option metadata, must not be null.
        Returns:
        the option value or default value if option is unknown
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - for unsupported option value types
        See Also:
        consumable(Class), OptionMetadata

      • save

        <V> void save(V value,
              OptionMetadata<V> option)
        Saves the value of specified option to the enclosed storage.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the value type for the option
        Parameters:
        value - to be saved, must not be null.
        option - the option metadata, must not be null.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - for unsupported option value types
        See Also:
        consumable(Class), OptionMetadata
